  "prompt": "What are the major aspects covered under ISO/TS 16949 Audit?",
  "response": "ISO/TS 16949 is a technical specification aimed at the development of a quality management system that facilitates continual improvement, defect prevention, and the reduction of variation and waste in the automotive industry supply chain. The major aspects covered under an ISO/TS 16949 audit typically include:\n\n1. **Quality Management System (QMS) Requirements**:\n   - Review of the documented Quality Management System.\n   - Assessment of quality policies, objectives, and the effectiveness of the QMS.\n\n2. **Management Responsibility**:\n   - Evaluation of top management commitment to the QMS.\n   - Examination of planning and communication processes.\n\n3. **Resource Management**:\n   - Assessment of human resources, including employee competency and training.\n   - Physical resources, infrastructure, work environment.\n\n4. **Product Realization**:\n   - Review of processes from design and development to delivery.\n   - Examination of customer-related processes and requirements.\n   - Analysis of production and service provision.\n\n5. **Measurement, Analysis, and Improvement**:\n   - Inspection of monitoring and measurement of processes and products.\n   - Evaluation of internal audits, corrective and preventive actions.\n   - Review of data analysis and continuous improvement initiatives.\n\n6. **Customer Focus**:\n   - Assessment of procedures for determining customer requirements and satisfaction.\n   - Effectiveness of customer communication.\n\n7. **Design and Development**:\n   - Review of design and development planning, inputs, outputs, and verification processes.\n   - Control of design changes.\n\n8. **Supply Chain Management**:\n   - Supplier selection, evaluation, and monitoring.\n   - Ensuring the quality of purchased products and services.\n\n9. **Production and Process Control**:\n   - Review of production workflows, controls, and process validation.\n   - Inspection of traceability and identification.\n\n10. **Internal Auditing and Continuous Improvement**:\n    - Routine assessment of internal audits and methods for continual improvement.\n    - Review of corrective and preventive actions.\n\nEach of these aspects ensures that the organization maintains high-quality standards, fulfills customer requirements, and improves its processes continuously. The audit is meticulous and spans all areas impacting quality within the automotive sector.",
